      • feed

        public int feed(byte[] buf)
        Description copied from interface: JsonFeeder
        Provide more data to the JsonParser. The method will consume as many bytes from the input buffer as possible, either until all bytes have been consumed or until the feeder is full (see JsonFeeder.isFull()). The method will return the number of bytes consumed (which can be 0 if the parser does not accept more input at the moment).
        Specified by:
        feed in interface JsonFeeder
        Parameters:
        buf - the byte array containing the data to consume
        Returns:
        the number of bytes consumed (can be 0 if the parser does not accept more input at the moment, see JsonFeeder.isFull())

      • feed

        public int feed(byte[] buf,
                int offset,
                int len)
        Description copied from interface: JsonFeeder
        Provide more data to the JsonParser. The method will consume as many bytes from the input buffer as possible, either until len bytes have been consumed or until the feeder is full (see JsonFeeder.isFull()). The method will return the number of bytes consumed (which can be 0 if the parser does not accept more input at the moment).
        Specified by:
        feed in interface JsonFeeder
        Parameters:
        buf - the byte array containing the data to consume
        offset - the start offset in the byte array
        len - the number of bytes to consume
        Returns:
        the number of bytes consumed (can be 0 if the parser does not accept more input at the moment, see JsonFeeder.isFull())

      • isFull

        public boolean isFull()
        Description copied from interface: JsonFeeder
        Checks if the parser accepts more input at the moment. If it doesn't, you have to call JsonParser.nextEvent() until it returns JsonEvent.NEED_MORE_INPUT. Only then new input can be provided to the parser.
        Specified by:
        isFull in interface JsonFeeder
        Returns:
        true if the parser does not accept more input
